https://jam.dev/

Jam is a software testing tool designed to streamline bug reporting and communication between developers and QA teams.
It automates the process of capturing crucial information such as device details, browser information, console logs, network logs, and backend tracing. 
The tool also offers features like automatic reproduction steps and visual bug recordings, making it easy to report bugs without technical knowledge.
Key features include:
Instant replay: Capture screen recordings of bugs.
Automatic logs: Collect browser console and network logs automatically.
Easy sharing: Share bug reports with annotated videos, logs, and repro steps.
Integrations: Works with tools like GitHub, Jira, Slack, and Sentry.
Jam helps teams save time by automating manual tasks and simplifying bug reproduction, enhancing productivity for both QA and development teams.
